</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C339E1AB8F2BFF9FFF1CF91EFE6CDFA2" pageId="2" pageNumber="565" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B9CB2208F2BFF9FFF1CF91EFE6CDFA2" blockId="2.[151,1444,1713,2028]" pageId="2" pageNumber="565">
<emphasis id="B9576E328F2BFF9FFF1CF91EFEBFDE82" bold="true" box="[151,274,1713,1739]" pageId="2" pageNumber="565">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
In dorsal view, head 1.6 × as wide as long; eye length 4.9 × temple; and eye length 1.7 × its width; ocelli in high triangle, POL: OD: OOL= 3: 5: 4 (
<figureCitation id="1318AEA58F2BFF9FFD58F97AFCBADEA6" box="[723,791,1749,1775]" captionStart="FIGURES 2–11" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1889,1913]" captionTargetBox="[196,1391,270,1863]" captionTargetId="figure-74@4.[196,1391,270,1863]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 2–11. Megalommum hoabinhense Long, sp. nov., holotype, female. 2 Head, frontal view 3 Head, dorsal view 4 Head, lateral view 5 Fore wing 6 Hind wing 7 Mesonotum 8 Metasoma 9 Hind femur 10 Ovipositor 11 First metasomal tergite." pageId="2" pageNumber="565">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
); vein 1-M of fore wing thin, 0.9 × vein 1-CU1 (
<figureCitation id="1318AEA58F2BFF9FFAC3F97AFA20DEB9" box="[1352,1421,1749,1776]" captionStart="FIGURES 2–11" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1889,1913]" captionTargetBox="[196,1391,270,1863]" captionTargetId="figure-74@4.[196,1391,270,1863]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 2–11. Megalommum hoabinhense Long, sp. nov., holotype, female. 2 Head, frontal view 3 Head, dorsal view 4 Head, lateral view 5 Fore wing 6 Hind wing 7 Mesonotum 8 Metasoma 9 Hind femur 10 Ovipositor 11 First metasomal tergite." pageId="2" pageNumber="565">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
); vein m-cu slightly curved inwards, and 1.2 × vein 1-M; basal length of second submarginal cell 4.3 × apical width; in lateral view, mesosoma 1.9 × its height; hind femur robust, 3.2 × its maximum width (
<figureCitation id="1318AEA58F2BFF9FFB0CF8B2FB61DF7E" box="[1159,1228,1821,1847]" captionStart="FIGURES 2–11" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1889,1913]" captionTargetBox="[196,1391,270,1863]" captionTargetId="figure-74@4.[196,1391,270,1863]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 2–11. Megalommum hoabinhense Long, sp. nov., holotype, female. 2 Head, frontal view 3 Head, dorsal view 4 Head, lateral view 5 Fore wing 6 Hind wing 7 Mesonotum 8 Metasoma 9 Hind femur 10 Ovipositor 11 First metasomal tergite." pageId="2" pageNumber="565">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
); mesoscutum flat posteriorly, with sparse fine punctures (
<figureCitation id="1318AEA58F2BFF9FFDD2F8EEFD32DF15" box="[601,671,1857,1884]" captionStart="FIGURES 2–11" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1889,1913]" captionTargetBox="[196,1391,270,1863]" captionTargetId="figure-74@4.[196,1391,270,1863]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 2–11. Megalommum hoabinhense Long, sp. nov., holotype, female. 2 Head, frontal view 3 Head, dorsal view 4 Head, lateral view 5 Fore wing 6 Hind wing 7 Mesonotum 8 Metasoma 9 Hind femur 10 Ovipositor 11 First metasomal tergite." pageId="2" pageNumber="565">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
); first metasomal tergite length 1.5 × its apical width, with median area striate-rugulose in most part, coriaceous apically; second tergite finely sculptured; midbasal triangular area of second tergite smooth, with punctate convergent grooves (
<figureCitation id="1318AEA58F2BFF9FFCCCF826FC26DFEA" box="[839,907,1929,1955]" captionStart="FIGURES 2–11" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1889,1913]" captionTargetBox="[196,1391,270,1863]" captionTargetId="figure-74@4.[196,1391,270,1863]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 2–11. Megalommum hoabinhense Long, sp. nov., holotype, female. 2 Head, frontal view 3 Head, dorsal view 4 Head, lateral view 5 Fore wing 6 Hind wing 7 Mesonotum 8 Metasoma 9 Hind femur 10 Ovipositor 11 First metasomal tergite." pageId="2" pageNumber="565">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
); second metasomal suture crenulate medially; third tergite sculptured laterally, smooth medially; ovipositor straight (
<figureCitation id="1318AEA58F2BFF9FFC25F802FBAFDF8E" box="[942,1026,1965,1991]" captionStart="FIGURES 2–11" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1889,1913]" captionTargetBox="[196,1391,270,1863]" captionTargetId="figure-74@4.[196,1391,270,1863]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 2–11. Megalommum hoabinhense Long, sp. nov., holotype, female. 2 Head, frontal view 3 Head, dorsal view 4 Head, lateral view 5 Fore wing 6 Hind wing 7 Mesonotum 8 Metasoma 9 Hind femur 10 Ovipositor 11 First metasomal tergite." pageId="2" pageNumber="565">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
); ovipositor sheath obliquely setose, 0.2 × as long as fore wing.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
