<caption id="DF5CE2A88F2AFF9EFF1CFC50FB6EDC52" box="[151,1219,1023,1051]" pageId="3" pageNumber="566" startId="3.[151,260,1023,1049]" targetBox="[340,1247,234,999]" targetPageId="3">
<paragraph id="8B9CB2208F2AFF9EFF1CFC50FB6EDC52" blockId="3.[151,1219,1023,1051]" box="[151,1219,1023,1051]" pageId="3" pageNumber="566">
<emphasis id="B9576E328F2AFF9EFF1CFC50FE8CDC50" bold="true" box="[151,289,1023,1049]" pageId="3" pageNumber="566">FIGURE 1.</emphasis>
Habitus of 
<taxonomicName id="4C23C9A38F2AFF9EFE39FBAFFC86DC53" authority="Long" authorityName="Dzuong &amp; Long &amp; Mai &amp; Hoa &amp; Oanh &amp; Nghiep" authorityYear="2022" box="[434,811,1024,1050]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Megalommum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="566" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hoabinhense" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B9576E328F2AFF9EFE39FBAFFD4ADC53" box="[434,743,1024,1050]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="566">Megalommum hoabinhense</emphasis>
Long
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A264D3498F2AFF9EFCBDFBAFFC3DDC53" box="[822,912,1024,1050]" pageId="3" pageNumber="566" rank="species">
<emphasis id="B9576E328F2AFF9EFCBDFBAFFC26DC53" bold="true" box="[822,907,1024,1050]" pageId="3" pageNumber="566">sp. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, holotype, female (lateral).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<subSubSection id="C339E1AB8F2AFF98FF4CFBE8FC9CDAE0" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="568" pageId="3" pageNumber="566" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B9CB2208F2AFF9EFF4CFBE8FEE2DCCF" blockId="3.[151,1437,1095,2023]" pageId="3" pageNumber="566">
<emphasis id="B9576E328F2AFF9EFF4CFBE8FEFCDC28" bold="true" box="[199,337,1095,1121]" pageId="3" pageNumber="566">Description</emphasis>
. 
<typeStatus id="54980C828F2AFF9EFEEBFBE7FE66DC2B" box="[352,459,1096,1122]" pageId="3" pageNumber="566">Holotype</typeStatus>
, female, length of body 7.0 mm, fore wing 
<quantity id="4CDB1FC58F2AFF9EFC3EFBE7FBA0DC2B" box="[949,1037,1096,1122]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.1" pageId="3" pageNumber="566" unit="mm" value="8.1">8.1 mm</quantity>
, antenna 
<quantity id="4CDB1FC58F2AFF9EFBFCFBE7FB7DDC2B" box="[1143,1232,1096,1122]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.4" pageId="3" pageNumber="566" unit="mm" value="8.4">8.4 mm</quantity>
, ovipositor sheath 
<quantity id="4CDB1FC58F2AFF9EFF1CFBC3FF40DCCF" box="[151,237,1132,1158]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.9" pageId="3" pageNumber="566" unit="mm" value="1.9">1.9 mm</quantity>
(
<figureCitation id="1318AEA58F2AFF9EFF77FBC3FE90DCCF" box="[252,317,1132,1158]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,260,1023,1049]" captionTargetBox="[340,1247,234,999]" captionTargetId="figure-43@3.[340,1247,234,999]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Habitus of Megalommum hoabinhense Long, sp. nov., holotype, female (lateral)." pageId="3" pageNumber="566">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9CB2208F2AFF9EFF4CFB3FFE90DE7F" blockId="3.[151,1437,1095,2023]" pageId="3" pageNumber="566">
<emphasis id="B9576E328F2AFF9EFF4CFB3FFEAADCE3" bold="true" box="[199,263,1168,1194]" pageId="3" pageNumber="566">Head</emphasis>
. Antenna with 62 flagellomeres, slightly longer fore wing; apical antennomere with distinct spine; in lateral view, scapus 1.6 × as long as wide; length of first flagellomere 1.1 × second; first, second and penultimate flagellomeres 1.3, 1.2 and 1.7 × their maximum width,; maxillary palp as long as height of head; head 1.3 and 1.6 × as wide as long in anterior (frontal) and dorsal view respectively; face narrowed medially, rugose, 0.6 × as wide as long (15: 24) (
<figureCitation id="1318AEA58F2AFF9EFECAFA8FFE2BDD73" box="[321,390,1312,1338]" captionStart="FIGURES 2–11" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1889,1913]" captionTargetBox="[196,1391,270,1863]" captionTargetId="figure-74@4.[196,1391,270,1863]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 2–11. Megalommum hoabinhense Long, sp. nov., holotype, female. 2 Head, frontal view 3 Head, dorsal view 4 Head, lateral view 5 Fore wing 6 Hind wing 7 Mesonotum 8 Metasoma 9 Hind femur 10 Ovipositor 11 First metasomal tergite." pageId="3" pageNumber="566">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
); in frontal view, eye length 2.2 × as long as its transverse width (38: 17); clypeus separated from face with a transverse carina; height of clypeus: inter tentorial distance: tentorial ocular distance = 5: 9: 3; distance between tentorial pits 3.0 × as long as distance from tentorial pit to eye margin (
<figureCitation id="1318AEA58F2AFF9EFBF7FAC7FB6DDDCB" box="[1148,1216,1384,1410]" captionStart="FIGURES 2–11" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1889,1913]" captionTargetBox="[196,1391,270,1863]" captionTargetId="figure-74@4.[196,1391,270,1863]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 2–11. Megalommum hoabinhense Long, sp. nov., holotype, female. 2 Head, frontal view 3 Head, dorsal view 4 Head, lateral view 5 Fore wing 6 Hind wing 7 Mesonotum 8 Metasoma 9 Hind femur 10 Ovipositor 11 First metasomal tergite." pageId="3" pageNumber="566">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
); malar space 0.5 × basal width of mandible; in lateral view, transverse width of eye 3.3 × as long as temple (30: 9) (
<figureCitation id="1318AEA58F2AFF9EFB54FA23FA88DDEF" box="[1247,1317,1420,1446]" captionStart="FIGURES 2–11" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1889,1913]" captionTargetBox="[196,1391,270,1863]" captionTargetId="figure-74@4.[196,1391,270,1863]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 2–11. Megalommum hoabinhense Long, sp. nov., holotype, female. 2 Head, frontal view 3 Head, dorsal view 4 Head, lateral view 5 Fore wing 6 Hind wing 7 Mesonotum 8 Metasoma 9 Hind femur 10 Ovipositor 11 First metasomal tergite." pageId="3" pageNumber="566">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
); in dorsal view, length of eye 4.9 × temple (34: 7); eye height 1.7 × its width; ocelli in high triangle, distance between anterior and posterior ocelli as long as OOL; POL: OD: OOL= 3: 5: 4 (
<figureCitation id="1318AEA58F2AFF9EFCE3FA7BFC06DDA7" box="[872,939,1492,1518]" captionStart="FIGURES 2–11" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1889,1913]" captionTargetBox="[196,1391,270,1863]" captionTargetId="figure-74@4.[196,1391,270,1863]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 2–11. Megalommum hoabinhense Long, sp. nov., holotype, female. 2 Head, frontal view 3 Head, dorsal view 4 Head, lateral view 5 Fore wing 6 Hind wing 7 Mesonotum 8 Metasoma 9 Hind femur 10 Ovipositor 11 First metasomal tergite." pageId="3" pageNumber="566">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
); vertex smooth, sparsely punctate, sparsely setose, not emarginated beyond antennal sockets; frons smooth, distinctly depressed laterally, with fine median carina (
<figureCitation id="1318AEA58F2AFF9EFF60F9B3FE82DE7F" box="[235,303,1564,1590]" captionStart="FIGURES 2–11" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1889,1913]" captionTargetBox="[196,1391,270,1863]" captionTargetId="figure-74@4.[196,1391,270,1863]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 2–11. Megalommum hoabinhense Long, sp. nov., holotype, female. 2 Head, frontal view 3 Head, dorsal view 4 Head, lateral view 5 Fore wing 6 Hind wing 7 Mesonotum 8 Metasoma 9 Hind femur 10 Ovipositor 11 First metasomal tergite." pageId="3" pageNumber="566">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9CB2208F2AFF9EFF4CF9EFFEE9DEA3" blockId="3.[151,1437,1095,2023]" pageId="3" pageNumber="566">
<emphasis id="B9576E328F2AFF9EFF4CF9EFFEE8DE13" bold="true" box="[199,325,1600,1626]" pageId="3" pageNumber="566">Mesosoma</emphasis>
. Mesosoma 1.9 × its height (62: 33); pronotum smooth laterally, setose; mesoscutum flat posteriorly, sparsely setose, with sparse fine punctures medially, almost smooth anteriorly and laterally (
<figureCitation id="1318AEA58F2AFF9EFB7BF9CBFA9ADE37" box="[1264,1335,1636,1662]" captionStart="FIGURES 2–11" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1889,1913]" captionTargetBox="[196,1391,270,1863]" captionTargetId="figure-74@4.[196,1391,270,1863]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 2–11. Megalommum hoabinhense Long, sp. nov., holotype, female. 2 Head, frontal view 3 Head, dorsal view 4 Head, lateral view 5 Fore wing 6 Hind wing 7 Mesonotum 8 Metasoma 9 Hind femur 10 Ovipositor 11 First metasomal tergite." pageId="3" pageNumber="566">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
); notauli shallow, smooth; scutellar sulcus narrow and shallow, crenulate; scutellum smooth, sparsely setose; mesopleuron and metapleuron smooth, setose; medial area of metanotum without midlongitudinal carina anteriorly; propodeum smooth, setose.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9CB2208F2AFF99FF4CF95CFD71D8B0" blockId="3.[151,1437,1095,2023]" lastBlockId="4.[151,1437,151,249]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="567" pageId="3" pageNumber="566">
<emphasis id="B9576E328F2AFF9EFF4CF95CFEBEDF44" bold="true" box="[199,275,1779,1805]" pageId="3" pageNumber="566">Wings</emphasis>
. Fore wing (
<figureCitation id="1318AEA58F2AFF9EFE2CF95BFE40DF47" box="[423,493,1779,1806]" captionStart="FIGURES 2–11" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1889,1913]" captionTargetBox="[196,1391,270,1863]" captionTargetId="figure-74@4.[196,1391,270,1863]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 2–11. Megalommum hoabinhense Long, sp. nov., holotype, female. 2 Head, frontal view 3 Head, dorsal view 4 Head, lateral view 5 Fore wing 6 Hind wing 7 Mesonotum 8 Metasoma 9 Hind femur 10 Ovipositor 11 First metasomal tergite." pageId="3" pageNumber="566">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
): length of pterostigma 5.0 × its width; vein 1-SR+M curved subbasally; vein 1-M thin, 0.9 × vein 1-CU1 (17: 18); vein 1-CU1 very thick, 3.0 × as thick as vein 1-M; vein 2-M curved basally; m-cu slightly curved inwards, and 1.2 × vein 1-M (
<figureCitation id="1318AEA58F2AFF9EFD1FF893FD74DF1F" box="[660,729,1851,1878]" captionStart="FIGURES 2–11" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1889,1913]" captionTargetBox="[196,1391,270,1863]" captionTargetId="figure-74@4.[196,1391,270,1863]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 2–11. Megalommum hoabinhense Long, sp. nov., holotype, female. 2 Head, frontal view 3 Head, dorsal view 4 Head, lateral view 5 Fore wing 6 Hind wing 7 Mesonotum 8 Metasoma 9 Hind femur 10 Ovipositor 11 First metasomal tergite." pageId="3" pageNumber="566">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
); subdiscal cell distinctly broader than discal cell, with median setose area and narrow glabrous sclerome, and upper and posterior parts of this area glabrous; veins SR1 curved subbasally; ratio of length of veins r: 3-RS: SR1 = 16: 41: 81; 2-RS: 3-RS: r-m = 24: 41: 15; second submarginal cell slightly narrowed apically, basal length of second submarginal cell 4.3 × its apical width; vein CU1b triangular, strongly widened basally (
<figureCitation id="1318AEA58F2AFF9EFE4EF863FDA6DFAF" box="[453,523,1995,2022]" captionStart="FIGURES 2–11" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1889,1913]" captionTargetBox="[196,1391,270,1863]" captionTargetId="figure-74@4.[196,1391,270,1863]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 2–11. Megalommum hoabinhense Long, sp. nov., holotype, female. 2 Head, frontal view 3 Head, dorsal view 4 Head, lateral view 5 Fore wing 6 Hind wing 7 Mesonotum 8 Metasoma 9 Hind femur 10 Ovipositor 11 First metasomal tergite." pageId="3" pageNumber="566">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
); subdiscal (brachial) cell with median area setose, surround this area glabrous. Hind wing (
<figureCitation id="1318AEA58F2DFF99FEABFF38FECBD8FB" box="[288,358,151,178]" captionStart="FIGURES 2–11" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1889,1913]" captionTargetBox="[196,1391,270,1863]" captionTargetId="figure-74@4.[196,1391,270,1863]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 2–11. Megalommum hoabinhense Long, sp. nov., holotype, female. 2 Head, frontal view 3 Head, dorsal view 4 Head, lateral view 5 Fore wing 6 Hind wing 7 Mesonotum 8 Metasoma 9 Hind femur 10 Ovipositor 11 First metasomal tergite." pageId="4" pageNumber="567">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
): vein SR slightly curved subbasally, parallel-sided apically; subbasal cell setose; vein 1r-m almost straight; vein 2-SC+R vertical (
<figureCitation id="1318AEA58F2DFF99FDB9FF14FDD8D89F" box="[562,629,187,214]" captionStart="FIGURES 2–11" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1889,1913]" captionTargetBox="[196,1391,270,1863]" captionTargetId="figure-74@4.[196,1391,270,1863]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 2–11. Megalommum hoabinhense Long, sp. nov., holotype, female. 2 Head, frontal view 3 Head, dorsal view 4 Head, lateral view 5 Fore wing 6 Hind wing 7 Mesonotum 8 Metasoma 9 Hind femur 10 Ovipositor 11 First metasomal tergite." pageId="4" pageNumber="567">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
); vein 1-M widely curved basally (
<figureCitation id="1318AEA58F2DFF99FC70FF14FB92D89F" box="[1019,1087,187,214]" captionStart="FIGURES 2–11" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1889,1913]" captionTargetBox="[196,1391,270,1863]" captionTargetId="figure-74@4.[196,1391,270,1863]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 2–11. Megalommum hoabinhense Long, sp. nov., holotype, female. 2 Head, frontal view 3 Head, dorsal view 4 Head, lateral view 5 Fore wing 6 Hind wing 7 Mesonotum 8 Metasoma 9 Hind femur 10 Ovipositor 11 First metasomal tergite." pageId="4" pageNumber="567">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
); M+CU: 1-M: 1r-m = 13: 83: 26; apex of vein SC+R1 with three curved hamuli.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF5CE2A88F2DFF99FF1CF8CEFF72DF88" pageId="4" pageNumber="567" startId="4.[151,264,1889,1913]" targetBox="[196,1391,270,1863]" targetPageId="4">
<paragraph id="8B9CB2208F2DFF99FF1CF8CEFF72DF88" blockId="4.[151,1436,1889,2022]" pageId="4" pageNumber="567">
<emphasis id="B9576E328F2DFF99FF1CF8CEFEEEDF30" bold="true" box="[151,323,1889,1913]" pageId="4" pageNumber="567">
FIGURES 2 
<emphasis id="B9576E328F2DFF99FE95F8CDFE86DF30" bold="true" box="[286,299,1890,1913]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="567">–</emphasis>
11
</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C23C9A38F2DFF99FED8F8CEFD1DDF33" authority="Long" authorityName="Dzuong &amp; Long &amp; Mai &amp; Hoa &amp; Oanh &amp; Nghiep" authorityYear="2022" box="[339,688,1889,1914]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Megalommum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="567" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hoabinhense" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B9576E328F2DFF99FED8F8CEFDC3DF30" box="[339,622,1889,1913]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="567">Megalommum hoabinhense</emphasis>
Long
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A264D3498F2DFF99FD35F8CEFCBEDF30" box="[702,787,1889,1913]" pageId="4" pageNumber="567" rank="species">
<emphasis id="B9576E328F2DFF99FD35F8CEFCA0DF30" bold="true" box="[702,781,1889,1913]" pageId="4" pageNumber="567">sp. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, holotype, female. 
<emphasis id="B9576E328F2DFF99FC69F8CEFC42DF30" bold="true" box="[994,1007,1889,1913]" pageId="4" pageNumber="567">2</emphasis>
Head, frontal view 
<emphasis id="B9576E328F2DFF99FB4CF8CEFB79DF30" bold="true" box="[1223,1236,1889,1913]" pageId="4" pageNumber="567">3</emphasis>
Head, dorsal view 
<emphasis id="B9576E328F2DFF99FF1CF82AFF09DFD4" bold="true" box="[151,164,1925,1949]" pageId="4" pageNumber="567">4</emphasis>
Head, lateral view 
<emphasis id="B9576E328F2DFF99FEF9F82AFED2DFD4" bold="true" box="[370,383,1925,1949]" pageId="4" pageNumber="567">5</emphasis>
Fore wing 
<emphasis id="B9576E328F2DFF99FE72F82AFDABDFD4" bold="true" box="[505,518,1925,1949]" pageId="4" pageNumber="567">6</emphasis>
Hind wing 
<emphasis id="B9576E328F2DFF99FD0EF82AFD3FDFD4" bold="true" box="[645,658,1925,1949]" pageId="4" pageNumber="567">7</emphasis>
Mesonotum 
<emphasis id="B9576E328F2DFF99FC90F82AFC85DFD4" bold="true" box="[795,808,1925,1949]" pageId="4" pageNumber="567">8</emphasis>
Metasoma 
<emphasis id="B9576E328F2DFF99FC20F82AFC15DFD4" bold="true" box="[939,952,1925,1949]" pageId="4" pageNumber="567">9</emphasis>
Hind femur 
<emphasis id="B9576E328F2DFF99FBCBF82AFBF4DFD4" bold="true" box="[1088,1113,1925,1949]" pageId="4" pageNumber="567">10</emphasis>
Ovipositor 
<emphasis id="B9576E328F2DFF99FB5CF82AFB42DFD4" bold="true" box="[1239,1263,1925,1949]" pageId="4" pageNumber="567">11</emphasis>
First metasomal tergite.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8B9CB2208F2DFF98FF4CF863FDE8D8B0" blockId="4.[151,1436,1889,2022]" lastBlockId="5.[151,1437,150,790]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="568" pageId="4" pageNumber="567">
<emphasis id="B9576E328F2DFF99FF4CF863FF52DFAF" bold="true" box="[199,255,1996,2022]" pageId="4" pageNumber="567">Legs</emphasis>
. Fore tibia 0.75 × fore tarsus (43: 57); ratio of lengths of fore femur: tibia: basitarsus: hind tarsus = 29: 43: 20: 57; hind femur robust, 3.2 × its maximum width (
<figureCitation id="1318AEA58F2CFF98FCA4FF38FCD9D8F8" box="[815,884,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURES 2–11" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1889,1913]" captionTargetBox="[196,1391,270,1863]" captionTargetId="figure-74@4.[196,1391,270,1863]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 2–11. Megalommum hoabinhense Long, sp. nov., holotype, female. 2 Head, frontal view 3 Head, dorsal view 4 Head, lateral view 5 Fore wing 6 Hind wing 7 Mesonotum 8 Metasoma 9 Hind femur 10 Ovipositor 11 First metasomal tergite." pageId="5" pageNumber="568">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
); femur, tibia, basitarsus 3.2, 10.9 and 6.0 × their maximum width; outer and inner hind tibial spurs 0.35 × and 0.4 × as long as hind basitarsus; respectively; tarsal claw simple and with bristly ventrally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9CB2208F2CFF98FF4CFEACFCECDA50" blockId="5.[151,1437,150,790]" pageId="5" pageNumber="568">
<emphasis id="B9576E328F2CFF98FF4CFEACFEEED954" bold="true" box="[199,323,259,285]" pageId="5" pageNumber="568">Metasoma</emphasis>
. First metasomal tergite 1.5 × as long as wide apically (41: 28), distinctly rugose with a midlongitudinal carina and a pair of narrow lateral smooth grooves; median area striate-rugulose in most part, coriaceous apically (
<figureCitation id="1318AEA58F2CFF98FF74FEE4FEFDD92C" box="[255,336,331,357]" captionStart="FIGURES 2–11" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1889,1913]" captionTargetBox="[196,1391,270,1863]" captionTargetId="figure-74@4.[196,1391,270,1863]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 2–11. Megalommum hoabinhense Long, sp. nov., holotype, female. 2 Head, frontal view 3 Head, dorsal view 4 Head, lateral view 5 Fore wing 6 Hind wing 7 Mesonotum 8 Metasoma 9 Hind femur 10 Ovipositor 11 First metasomal tergite." pageId="5" pageNumber="568">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
); second metasomal tergite 1.2 × as long as third tergite medially (25: 21), 1.4 × as wide (basally) as long (35: 25), length of midbasal triangular of second tergite in basal 0.8 of tergite (19: 25) (
<figureCitation id="1318AEA58F2CFF98FB34FEC0FAAFD9C0" box="[1215,1282,367,393]" captionStart="FIGURES 2–11" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1889,1913]" captionTargetBox="[196,1391,270,1863]" captionTargetId="figure-74@4.[196,1391,270,1863]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 2–11. Megalommum hoabinhense Long, sp. nov., holotype, female. 2 Head, frontal view 3 Head, dorsal view 4 Head, lateral view 5 Fore wing 6 Hind wing 7 Mesonotum 8 Metasoma 9 Hind femur 10 Ovipositor 11 First metasomal tergite." pageId="5" pageNumber="568">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
); lateral sides of midbasal triangular area surrounded by shallow convergent punctate grooves; antero-lateral depression wide, coriaceous (
<figureCitation id="1318AEA58F2CFF98FE95FE18FECFD998" box="[286,354,439,465]" captionStart="FIGURES 2–11" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1889,1913]" captionTargetBox="[196,1391,270,1863]" captionTargetId="figure-74@4.[196,1391,270,1863]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 2–11. Megalommum hoabinhense Long, sp. nov., holotype, female. 2 Head, frontal view 3 Head, dorsal view 4 Head, lateral view 5 Fore wing 6 Hind wing 7 Mesonotum 8 Metasoma 9 Hind femur 10 Ovipositor 11 First metasomal tergite." pageId="5" pageNumber="568">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
); second metasomal suture narrow, crenulate; third-fifth metasomal tergites coriaceous; ovipositor straight, needle-shaped apically, without dorsal notch or nodus and ventral serrations (
<figureCitation id="1318AEA58F2CFF98FBFDFE74FB64D9BC" box="[1142,1225,475,501]" captionStart="FIGURES 2–11" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1889,1913]" captionTargetBox="[196,1391,270,1863]" captionTargetId="figure-74@4.[196,1391,270,1863]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 2–11. Megalommum hoabinhense Long, sp. nov., holotype, female. 2 Head, frontal view 3 Head, dorsal view 4 Head, lateral view 5 Fore wing 6 Hind wing 7 Mesonotum 8 Metasoma 9 Hind femur 10 Ovipositor 11 First metasomal tergite." pageId="5" pageNumber="568">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
); ovipositor sheath covered with dense oblique setae, 0.2 × as long as fore wing.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9CB2208F2CFF98FF4CFD8DFC9CDAE0" blockId="5.[151,1437,150,790]" pageId="5" pageNumber="568">
<emphasis id="B9576E328F2CFF98FF4CFD8DFEB6DA75" bold="true" box="[199,283,546,572]" pageId="5" pageNumber="568">Colour</emphasis>
. Body yellow (
<figureCitation id="1318AEA58F2CFF98FE41FD8CFDA1DA74" box="[458,524,547,573]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,260,1023,1049]" captionTargetBox="[340,1247,234,999]" captionTargetId="figure-43@3.[340,1247,234,999]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Habitus of Megalommum hoabinhense Long, sp. nov., holotype, female (lateral)." pageId="5" pageNumber="568">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
); eyes black or dark brown; scapus and pedicellus yellow; flagellum dark brown in more than basal half, brownish yellow apically; pterostigma yellow with black spot apically; vein and membrane of fore wing yellow, except parastigma black and dark brown area between parastigma and base of vein 1-SR+M; all legs yellow; ovipositor sheath brown; ovipositor yellow.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
